New ILP Payment & ASN.1 OER CoDec Design (#28)

* New ILP Payment & ASN.1 OER CoDec Design
* Adds new models for InterledgerPayments and ILQP domain objects.
* Introduces a new Encoder/Decoder (Codec) design to more easily map from various ILP encodings (e.g., ASN.1 OER, JSON, Protobuf, etc) to Java ILP Core model objects like an InterledgerPayment.
* Re-structure the package naming scheme for better organization.
* Unit test coverage.

Fix #35 and #36 (#44)

* Move InterledgerPacket to top-level. InterledgerPacket is the top-level interface for objects that can be sent “on the wire” in the Interledger protocol suite.  Examples include InterledgerPayment and Quoting packets.
* Fix #35: Remove the “wire” package and move all codec-related interfaces/clases into the “org.interledger.codecs” package.
* Fix #36: Move “InterledgerPacket” to a top-level interledger namespace.  Move “Packet Handler” mechanisms to be internally-defined in InterledgerPacket for clarity.
* Add unit tests for InterledgerPacket.Handler abstract utility classes.

Misc
* Add package-info.java classes where appropriate.
* Formatting, package renames.
* Formatting to appease Checkstyle.

peptide-shaker Added --exec_dir option

The --exec_dir option specifies an alternate directory for the
peptide-shaker distribution.  If the option is used and the directory
does not exist, the script will copy the distribution to that directory.
PeptideShaker updates files relative to the path of the jar file. Thus
we
need to copy the jar file, lib, and resources to the working directory
when used in a multiuser environment such as galaxy.

Load article and edit preview html directly w/o javascript bridge.

 -Switched to single query article download - the reason is it
  is tricker to be splitting lead/non-lead section retrieval
  across 2 requests and also if the point of this refactor is
  to streamline away low-performance javascript, it seems
  antithetical to be amending/injecting late arriving
  non-lead section html via javascript. Additionally,
  now that we're using gzip encoding properly the download
  is much smaller than it was when we first split the
  request in 2.

  work anyway.

 -Vastly simplified css transforms. Turns out the wide table
  overflow transform is no longer needed at all! - upstream
  css takes care of it now apparently.

  should be more reliable.

  some css out to separate "styleoverrides.css" file.

Move monotonic_time to BPF class, use CLOCK_MONOTONIC

This allows all the tools (currently: trace and memleak) to use the
`monotonic_time` facility, with the fix to use `CLOCK_MONOTONIC`
instead of `CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW`. Resolves #931.

Simplify BCC symbol resolution API

The new API has two main methods: `sym` and `ksym` (the second is
a trivial wrapper of the first one). Both methods accept two
Boolean flags arguments: `show_module` and `show_address`. The first
controls whether the resulting symbol name should contain the name
of the symbol's module, in brackets. For kernel symbols, this is
simply "[kernel]". The second controls whether the resulting symbol
name should contain the instruction offset from the beginning of
the symbol, e.g. "start_thread+0x202".
